rComments: One of the worst Professors I have encountered. Unapproachable when you have issues and when you email him your concern he gives off a "you should've known better" vibe. Syllabus was not clear at the beginning then after the course is over mentions  key details regarding the participation mark. Says "all or nothing" at the end not 1% per class.
Extremely clear, makes material accessible if you just go and speak with him. Tests tend to be easy, marks fairly.
Patronizing and unapproachable. Lectures often involve irrelevant personal details about himself.

This class was taught in an engaging and interesting manner. Prof Freeman is a passionate and extraordinarily helpful teacher, not to mention EXTREMELY generous with allowances and understandings. It is unfair to rate him poorly based upon an inability to achieve the grade one "thinks" they deserve. Excellent class, beyond excellent professor.

The evaluations are really easy, but the grading was really unfair.  You may walk out of there thinking you wrote the best exam of your life, but receive a mark that reflects very little of what you wrote.  Worst part is, when you try to approach Dr. Freeman, he becomes very patronizing and says things such as "You should have known better."
